      "span_text": "Total body water (TBW) was determined by deuterium oxide (D 2 O) dilution following the Maastricht protocol.  Brie¯y, in the evening, prior to anthropometric measurements, after obtaining a background urine sample, subjects ingested an oral dose of D 2 O. Deuterium enrichment was measured in urine from the second voiding of the following morning."
